We recommended the following to the Management for a reliable Road Networks account in the financial statements:
Create an Inventory Committee to conduct an inventory of the local roads under the LGU’s jurisdiction and prepare Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System;
The Municipal Engineer shall provide the Municipal Accountant with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
The LGU shall maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and shall keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;
The Municipal Accountant shall prepare the Journal Voucher to record the inventory of the local road network and its components in the general ledger and the Local Road Network Ledger Card; keep and maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network, and ensure full disclosure of road networks in the Notes to the Financial Statements of the LGU.

