We recommended that management consider the following:
Prepare the contract of Lease between the LGU and the stall owners;
Ensure that the contract of lease includes the condition of cancellation of right to use the stalls in case of default in the payment of rental fee for considerable time and non-renewal on contract of lease;
The contract of lease also includes prohibition of sub-leasing the stalls to others without the approval of the LGU and the rent from sub-lease shall be an income of the LGU;
Ensure that the terms and conditions in the contract are strictly complied with;
Make strategies such as condonation of interest and penalties for full payment of arrears, payment by installment to be able to collect the amount of P16.781 million arrears from stall owners.

We recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
to intensify its collection of the real property tax receivables which had accumulated to P34.715 million;
the Municipal Treasurer conduct massive tax information campaign and exert efforts to ensure collection of all realty taxes; 
Demand letters should be sent regularly to the delinquent owners, and if warranted, their names including the amount of their realty tax delinquencies should be posted in public places for information of everyone in the locality.

